is known from the 
<typeStatus box="[625,730,152,178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
, collected in the vicinity of Bowen, north 
<collectingRegion box="[1233,1371,152,178]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 131" captionStartId="56.[151,255,1043,1067]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,279,985]" captionTargetId="figure-48@56.[220,1377,197,1028]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 131. Map of New Guinea and northeastern Australia showing distribution of: (․) Macrolema dickdaviesi sp. nov., (̝) M. giya sp. nov.; (●) M. karimui sp. nov." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 131</figureCitation>
), before 1919, when 
<collectorName box="[443,566,189,215]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. Simson</collectorName>
